cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with modeling and predicting election outcomes based on social networks and individual preferences, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

Firstly, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) seems like the most likely category, as the paper focuses on the role of social networks in shaping individual beliefs and preferences. 

Secondly, cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is also a strong possibility, as the paper discusses the impact of election outcomes on the economy and the population at large. 

Thirdly, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be a relevant category, as the paper proposes a mathematical model for analyzing election outcomes based on individual estimates and biases. 

Fourthly, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) could also be a relevant category, as the paper discusses different voting rules and their performance in reducing surprise in election outcomes. 

Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could be a relevant category, as the paper proposes a model for predicting election outcomes based on individual preferences and social networks, which could have applications in AI-based decision-making systems.
